description: Baru Gold Corporation engages in the exploration and evaluation assets in Indonesia. The company holds a 70% interest in Sangihe gold-silver project located on the island of Sangihe covering an area of 42,000 hectares. It also holds interest in the Miwah gold project that consists of three contiguous mining business permits covering an area of 30,000 hectares located to the southeast of Banda Aceh in Aceh Province. The company was formerly known as East Asia Minerals Corporation and changed its name to Baru Gold Corporation in October 2020. Baru Gold Corporation is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
